{"author":{"id":"c52cb19fb02c210e51792121b2bae318d19fa8efb308ae796946bf1f79891ad1"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1782779185,"nonce":"WNvn2/AL0gNdxJK5ypgR3LjYu5M=","title":"Named WINDOW clause (SELECT ‚Ä¶ OVER w ‚Ä¶ WINDOW w AS (‚Ä¶))","message":"Optional enhancement split out of cd51c6e (window functions). The core window-function support ‚Äî ROW_NUMBER/RANK/DENSE_RANK/NTILE/LAG/LEAD, aggregate-as-window, PARTITION BY, ORDER BY, and frame clauses (ROWS/RANGE BETWEEN) ‚Äî is complete. This tracks the *named* WINDOW clause: declaring a window definition once at the query level and referencing it by name from multiple expressions.\n\n  SELECT SUM(x) OVER w, AVG(y) OVER w FROM t WINDOW w AS (PARTITION BY a ORDER BY b ROWS ‚Ä¶)\n\n## Value / priority (low)\nLargely cosmetic. The inline `.over(|w| ‚Ä¶)` builder already covers all functional cases, and the DRY benefit is mostly achievable today by defining a reusable `Fn(Window) -\u003e Window` closure and passing it to several `.over()` calls ‚Äî each call gets a fresh Window. A named WINDOW clause only changes the *emitted SQL text* (one shared `WINDOW w AS (‚Ä¶)` instead of repeated inline `OVER (‚Ä¶)`), matching hand-written SQL; it adds no new query capability. So this is a nice-to-have for SQL readability/compactness, not a functional gap.\n\n## Why it's non-trivial\nIt touches the SELECT sink, not just the expression AST:\n- New query-level clause carrying the window definitions (mirror the OrderBy/GroupBy wrapper-struct + SelectAst/RenderSelectAst pattern in query.rs; new `WindowParams` assoc type accumulated via HAppend).\n- New `SelectSink::push_named_window(...)` + a `lower_windows_into` step rendered AFTER HAVING and BEFORE ORDER BY (standard SQL position). Implement in both SelectRenderSink (render.rs, shared by PG/MySQL) and TestSelectSink (squealy-test/src/sql.rs).\n- A way for a window expr to reference a named window instead of inlining ‚Äî extend visit_window / WindowExprAst to emit `OVER w`.\n- Thread named windows through the view model: add a `window_definitions` field to ViewQueryModel (model.rs), lower it in view.rs, render in view_render.rs, and round-trip in the squealy-model KDL serializer (package.rs).\n- PG and MySQL 8.0+ share the syntax, so likely no Dialect seam.\n\n## Public-API decision (the crux ‚Äî decide before building)\nThis builder is closure-based (`.select(|(t,)| ‚Ä¶)`), and the WINDOW clause is define-once/reference-many. Two main shapes:\n1. **String-named** ‚Äî `.window(\"w\", |(t,)| Window::new().partition_by(‚Ä¶)‚Ä¶)` + `expr.over_name(\"w\")`. Simple, SQL-like, but referencing an undeclared name is only caught at execution, not compile time (off-ethos for this crate).\n2. **Typed handle** ‚Äî a window handle threaded into the `.select()`/`.order_by()` closures so a reference proves the window exists. Fully type-safe (in keeping with the crate) but invasive: the existing closure signatures take only the source-column tuple, so this needs a parallel select/order_by family or an arity change.\n\nRecommend deciding 1 vs 2 up front; lean typed-handle for consistency with the crate's compile-time-check ethos, but it's the larger change.\n\n## Architecture pointers (from an exploration done 2026-06-30)\n- SelectAst / RenderSelectAst traits: query.rs ~5150‚Äì5267; render order sources‚Üífilters‚Üígroups‚Üíhavings‚Üíorders‚Üíbounds.\n- Clause-wrapper pattern to mirror: OrderBy struct query.rs ~5642, its SelectAst/RenderSelectAst impls ~6297‚Äì6420 (custom lower_orders_into).\n- SelectSink trait: query.rs ~3815‚Äì3916. SelectRenderSink: render.rs ~299‚Äì350 (streaming writes; finish() does LIMIT/OFFSET/lock). TestSelectSink: squealy-test/src/sql.rs ~136‚Äì304.\n- Window expr/visitor: WindowExprAst + visit_window in expr.rs; renderers in render.rs ~2246, squealy-test/src/sql.rs ~1423, param-collector query.rs ~4836, view lowering view.rs.\n- View model: ViewQueryModel model.rs ~544 (no window_definitions field yet); view_render.rs ~435; KDL ser/de 